I can't believe I had this experience at Chipotle. Attached is my receipt. You can see that my order was placed b/w 12:30 and 12:45. My receipt wasn't even printed until 1:29 p.m and the "promise ready to pick up time" is 1:00 p.m. I walked into the store at 1:20 p.m.  When someone finally decided to pay attention to me and asks me what I needed, I told them that I am waiting on an order because the pickup order shelves were empty. I showed the cashier my order on the app and even gave her my phone. And she said "I don't see your name what's your name?" Even though I had already given my name, I showed her under my account setting my name. That's when she printed off the receipt to give it to one of the assembly line people to make. I'm sorry. If I wanted to watch my food being made, I would have placed the order in the restaurant. Not on the app. This literally null and voids the purpose of your app if your employees can't fulfill pick up orders. On top of all of this, I never got an apology or anything. Just a "Here's your food." How inconsiderate! You can't even acknowledge you made a mistake and is causing a delay. This is so inexcusable!
